This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on November 2, 2011. The memorandum delegates authority to the Secretary of State and the Director of National Intelligence to submit certification and reports related to the New START Treaty. The Secretary of State is directed to make an annual certification and submit it, along with a report prepared by the Director of National Intelligence, to the Senate. The Secretary of State is also directed to submit reports to the Committees on Foreign Relations and Armed Services of the Senate. The memorandum concludes by authorizing the Secretary of State to publish it in the Federal Register.